_:N0c6d9a87e47942758a6fe75bc0144e93 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Mark Hoban was appointed Minister of State for Employment in September 2012. He was elected Conservative MP for Fareham on 7 June 2001.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"education\">Education</h3>\n\n<p>Mark has an economics degree from the London School of Economics.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"political-career\">Political career</h3>\n\n<p>Mark was Shadow Minister for Schools from 2003 to 2005 and Shadow Financial Secretary to the Treasury from 2005 to 2010. In May 2010, he was appointed Financial Secretary to the Treasury.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"career-outside-politics\">Career outside politics</h3>\n\n<p>After graduating, Mark qualified as a chartered accountant. He previously worked for PricewaterhouseCoopers, where he was a senior manager.</p>\n\n" .
